Our favorite member of the staff was Mary who spent as much time with us as we needed in mapping out our daily itinerary to shops, galleries, restaurants, sightseeing highlights, bicycling paths, historic homes, and etc.	We have stayed at other hotels in KW, but by far this is our favorite.	We ate very well in Key West, but our favorite meal was at Cafe Marquesa.	Although we had a convertible for transportation, we preferred using our rental bicycles because of the Inn's strategic location in Old Key West where all the action was.	But really, our favorite activity is sitting by the gorgeous patio and pools, drinking iced tea, and talking to fellow guests.